HyperMegaCyber
==============

Basic hybrid Monte-Carlo for python.

This code is heavily inspired by the [deep learning tutorials with theano][1]
and [Radford Neal's work for R][2].


Dependencies
------------

The only dependency is [numpy][3].


Installation
------------

Run 

    $ python setup.py install

or alternatively

    $ pip install .

from the source directory. You might have to prefix the call with a `sudo`.


[1]: http://deeplearning.net/tutorial/hmc.html
[2]: http://www.cs.toronto.edu/~radford/ham-mcmc-simple
[3]: http://numpy.org
